msIdentifier.collection: John Frederick Lewis Collection of European Manuscripts

msContents.summary: This manuscript contains a late fourteenth-century copy of the treatise Tractatus moralis de virtutibus (Moral Tract on the Virtues).

msItem.title: Tractatus moralis de virtutibus (Moral Tract on the Virtues)
msItem.author: Guilelmus Peraldus, approximately 1190-1271

msItem.title: Tractatus moralis de virtutibus (Moral Tract on the Virtues)

supportDesc.extent: ii+230+ii; 152 x 104 mm bound to 164 x 110 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto; numbering (in a later hand) extant lower corner recto

p.catchwords: Pages have been cut; some evidence of numbering in the center of the lower margin verso, but no catchwords extant

layoutDesc.layout: Frame-ruled in ink; two columns of forty lines; pricking extant; written area: 112 x 104 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Eight-line puzzle initial with pen flourishing in red and blue (fol. 1r); two-line pen-flourished initials in red and blue throughout; paragraph signs in red and blue; rubrication throughout; some marginalia
58vMarginal note, French, 15th c. hand: "faulte d'argent douleur non pareille mais argent prent villes et chasteaux."

binding.p: English brown calf, circa 1830, blind tooled with gothic design on the sides, half red morocco case

history.provenance: Fifteenth-century marginal note in French (fol. 58); No. 12 in a modern English bookseller's cat. (Â£ 4.15.00); (directly to?) John Frederick Lewis, Philadelphia; given by his widow, Anne Baker Lewis, to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1936
